The first argument to `replaceAll` is a regular expression.  Which means that when you&#39;re looking for 

    &quot;(clientSecret\\*\&quot;:\\*\&quot;)[^\&quot;]*&quot;

you need to escape the backslashes from the regular expression parser, as well as from the Java compiler.  In other words, to match a single backslash in the target, you need to write four backslashes in your Java.  The term you match should have been written as

    &quot;(clientSecret\\\\*\&quot;:\\\\*\&quot;)[^\&quot;]*&quot;

Otherwise, you&#39;re actually matching a single asterisk, each time you intended to match multiple backslashes.

